Protozoans similar in morphology to members of the genus 

Cothurnia

(
Vaginicolidae
) were attached to the pereopods of 

Progebiophilus upogebiae

from the Gulf of Mexico (
Fig. 6C, D
). In addition, these bopyrid specimens had mesomycetozoeans (Class Mesomycetozoea, Order Eccrinales) attached to the cuticle (
Fig. 6C
). Such ectosymbionts have previously been reported from other bopyrids (Williams & An 2009) and their hosts (

Shields 
et al
. 2015

).
